d billing information.\\r\\nInformation submitted as a part of a survey, blog comment or providing support.\\r\\nPersonal data collected from publicly available resources such as, not limited to, from Facebook, LinkedIn, Twitter and Google.\\r\\nWe may post a customer’s testimonials and comments on our Website which may contain personal information. Prior to posting We obtain the Customer’s consent.\\r\\n\\u003ch4\\u003e2. Navigational information\\u003c/h4\\u003e\\r\\nThis refers to information about your computer and your visits to our website such as, not limited to, your IP address, geographical location, browser type, referral source, length of visit and pages viewed.\\r\\nWe also may use technologies such as Cookies (see Cookies Policy) that collect information about your online activities over time. The information we collect automatically is statistical data and does not include personal information. It helps us to improve our Website and to deliver a better and more personalized service.\\r\\n\\u003ch4\\u003e3. Special category information\\u003c/h4\\u003e\\r\\nWe do not collect data which may be considered “special” or “sensitive” (e.g. genetic data, biometric data, data revealing racial or ethnic origin, political opinions, religion or other beliefs, health-related data, trade-union membership) unless it is volunteered by you.\\r\\n\\u003ch3\\u003eHow to use your information\\u003c/h3\\u003e\\r\\nWe use the information we collect or you provide to us only in compliance with the Privacy Policy for the following purposes:\\r\\n\\u003cul\\u003e\\r\\n \\t\\u003cli\\u003eTo provide you with information and services that you request from us;\\u003c/li\\u003e\\r\\n \\t\\u003cli\\u003eTo perform the contractual relationship;\\u003c/li\\u003e\\r\\n \\t\\u003cli\\u003eTo inform you about our services and updates;\\u003c/li\\u003e\\r\\n \\t\\u003cli\\u003eTo invite you to upcoming company events;\\u003c/li\\u003e\\r\\n \\t\\u003cli\\u003eTo conduct marketing surveys or market analysis;\\u003c/li\\u003e\\r\\n \\t\\u003cli\\u003eFor any other purpose with your consent.\\u003c/li\\u003e\\r\\n\\u003c/ul\\u003e\\r\\n\\u003ch3\\u003eTransfer and disclosure of your information\\u003c/h3\\u003e\\r\\nWe may disclose or share your personal information with our 1/ employees who directly work on your project; 2/ business partners who are bound by an NDA\'s agreements to keep personal information confidential and use it only for the purposes for which we disclose it to them. Navigational data can be accessed by marketing employees for improving the website functionality.\\r\\n\\u003ch3\\u003eData Security\\u003c/h3\\u003e\\r\\nWe use reasonable organizational, technical and administrative measures to protect your personal information from unauthorized access, use or disclosure. However, no data transmission over the internet or data storage system can be guaranteed to be 100% secure. If you have any questions about the security of your personal information or you feel that the security of any data that we hold about you has been compromised, please contact us at [hello@umind.tech].\\r\\n\\u003ch3\\u003eRetention of your personal data\\u003c/h3\\u003e\\r\\nWe retain personal information that you provide us for as long as it is necessary for the purposes for which it was collected and/or processed, or as required to do so by law.\\r\\n\\u003ch3\\u003eYour rights\\u003c/h3\\u003e\\r\\nUnder the General Data Protection Regulation if you provide your personal information you have the following rights with respect to this information:\\r\\n\\u003cul\\u003e\\r\\n \\t\\u003cli\\u003eRight to access the information that you have supplied to us; \\u003c/li\\u003e\\r\\n \\t\\u003cli\\u003eRight to request that we correct information you believe is inaccurate or incomplete; \\u003c/li\\u003e\\r\\n \\t\\u003cli\\u003eRight to erase the personal information you provided to us; \\u003c/li\\u003e\\r\\n \\t\\u003cli\\u003eRight to restrict the processing of your personal data; \\u003c/li\\u003e\\r\\n \\t\\u003cli\\u003eRight to object to how we manage your information; \\u003c/li\\u003e\\r\\n \\t\\u003cli\\u003eRight to request us to transfer the data that we have collected to another organization or directly to you. \\u003c/li\\u003e\\r\\n\\u003c/ul\\u003e\\r\\nIf you would like to exercise any of these rights, please contact us at our [hello@umind.tech].\\r\\n\\u003ch3\\u003eCookies Policy\\u003c/h3\\u003e\\r\\nCookies are small text files placed on your computer/device allowing us to collect log information and browsing activities. We use first-party cookies to monitor how visitors use our website, number of their visits and determine the popularity of certain content. Cookies are used by Google analytics which allows us to analyze the collected non-personal information. Entering our Website you may accept or refuse using cookies. Please note that if you refuse cookies some features of our website can be inaccessible or displayed improperly.\\r\\n\\u003ch3\\u003ePrivacy policies of other websites\\u003c/h3\\u003e\\r\\nOur Company website contains links to other websites. Our privacy policy applies only to our website, so if you click on a link to another website, you should read their privacy policy.\\r\\n\\u003ch3\\u003eChanges to our privacy policy\\u003c/h3\\u003e\\r\\nOur Company keeps its privacy policy under regular review and places any updates on this web page.\\r\\n\\u003ch3\\u003eHow to Contact us\\u003c/h3\\u003e\\r\\nIf you have any questions about our privacy policy, the data we hold on you, or you would like to exercise one of your data protection rights, please do not hesitate to contact us.\\r\\nEmail us: hello@umind.tech\\r\\nCall us: tel: +48786422678\\r\\nOr Write to us at: Poland, Warsaw, 02-972 Adama Branickiego Str. 21, Suite U3.\\r\\n","_description":"field_649b22ecd82c1"},"mode":"edit"} /-->', 'Privacy Policy', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '334-revision-v1', '', '', '2023-06-29 17